      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British pound falls after a weak retail sales report reinforces expectations that US interest rates will rise faster than those in Britain; in New York, pound settles at $1.4819, down from $1.4930; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>POUND SLIDES. The pound fell after a weak retail sales report reinforced expectations that United States interest rates will rise faster than those in Britain. In New York, the pound settled at $1.4819, down from $1.4930.</p>
      </block>
